President Obama has announced the appointment of three Deputy Associate Directors of the White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs: Jodi Archambault Gillette, Nicholas Rathod, and Michael Blake. Gillette previously served as the North Dakota First American Vote Director for the Obama Campaign for Change and has a background in Native American studies and public administration. Rathod has worked as the Director of Intergovernmental Affairs for the Obama-Biden Transition Project and has experience in community organizing and civil rights law. Blake worked on the Obama for America presidential campaign and has a background in journalism and political training. President Obama expressed confidence in their abilities to serve the American people and make the White House more open and transparent.